Angular Tutorial #9 - Decorators 

- TypeScript Feature used to passed meta Data.
- This are functions which will returns functions.
- Decorators are invoked at runtime.
- Decorators allows us to invoke functions
- All Decorators in Angular are represented with '@' Symbol.
	- @module
	- @Component
	- @Injectable
	- @Pipe
- define class Decorators, Input Decorators etc.
- These Decorators have Metadata.
	- has specific metadata.
	- some are mendatory and some are optional.

* Types 

- Class Decorators - @NgModule, @Component 
- Property Decorators - @Input, @Output
- Method Decorators - @HostListener
- Parameter Decorators - @Inject
